#3607
A Field of Bones~
   Likely the work of grave robbers searching for treasures or lucrative body
parts, someone has left these final resting spots in a desecrated upheaval.  
The grassy field of tombstones is littered with stained white bones, whole and
broken.  The dead do not rest peacefully in this part of the graveyard.  
Coffins lay half uncovered and mausoleum doors flap in the breeze.  
~
