#3615
The Headless Warrior~
   A life-sized statue of a nondescript soldier stands alone as a perfect
replica of the common soldier, minus his head.  The sculpture was meant to
honor the countless lives of common men who were conscripted to battle against
their will.  Looking closely, the statue almost appears to bleed from its
stone-carved cuts and wounds.  Looking behind the headless man, there appears
to be a mass grave but oddly enough, several holes seem to be burrowed out
from beneath the ground.  
~
