#3619
The General's Tomb~
   A regal tomb enshrined in decorative weapons and armored horses stands tall
against the horizon.  A sonnet inscribed on the large stone door regales a
tale of an esteemed warmaster felled in battle but never truly lain to rest.
There are footprints and tracks encircling the tomb, but no trail leading up
to it.  There are guard posts flanking the entrance to the tomb that look to
have been recently occupied.  
