#3640
A Simple Waiting Room~
   Just before the captain's office is a small sitting room.  There is a plain
wooden bench with seating for two in the corner surrounded by glass display
cases.  Each case contains various small weapons and a single decorative
military sabre.  A plaque on the front of each case briefly describes a
different, significant event from the city's history when the guard regiment
was brought to bare.  Right next to the bench is a large oak door leading to
the captain's office.  
~
